Mandible
(
Fig. 11D, E
). Coxa with slender elongate gnathobase (
Fig. 11D
); cutting edge with two large and four smaller teeth. Palp biramous (
Fig. 11E
). Basis asetose. Endopod two-segmented; proximal segment asetose, distal segment apically furnished with four naked, basally fused, slender setae. Exopod one-third length of endopod, one-segmented, with three apical setae.

Maxillule
(
Fig. 11F, G
). Praecoxal arthrite with two juxtaposed slender setae on anterior surface. Inner margin of arthrite with five stout spines (two of which shorter than the others) and four additional setae (not all visible in 
Fig. 11G
). Coxal endite bearing three slender setae. Endite of basis armed with three slender naked setae. Endopod one-segmented, with three slender naked setae. Exopod missing.

